The applicant for registration shall file with the department, a statement containing:
The name and address of the applicant and the name and address of the person whose name will appear on the label, if other than the applicant's;
The name of the pesticide and its EPA registration number;
A complete copy of the labeling accompanying the pesticide and a statement of all claims made or to be made for it including directions for use and a request that the pesticide be classified for nonrestricted use, for restricted use, or for both as provided for in FIFRA. In the case of renewal of registration, a statement shall be required only with respect to information which is different from that furnished when the pesticide was registered or last reregistered, unless the department requests a copy of the labeling; and
Other necessary information as specified by the department on the application for registration form.

section.section:
The annual fees received by the department shall be used to fund:
The Kentucky Agriculture and Environment in the Classroom program, a program administered by the department;
The farm chemical and container disposal program, a program administered by the department;
The cost-sharing program through the department and the Energy and Environment Cabinet, Division of Conservation, for the use of farmers in implementing agricultural production practices that protect the quality of soil and water resources; and
Expenses incurred in the enforcement of KRS 217.542 to 217.630.

text.section:
Upon certification by the administrator of EPA to register pesticides in accordance with Section 24(c) of FIFRA, the department may register the pesticides if it determines that:
Its composition warrants the proposed claims for it;
Its labeling and other material required to be submitted meet with the requirements of KRS 217.542 to 217.630;
It will perform its intended function, and when used in accordance with widespread and commonly recognized practice, will not cause unreasonable adverse effects on the environment; and
The registration is not disapproved by the administrator of EPA.
